changing the business. While Big Data are very well suited to run a business efficiently, Small Data lay open phenomena which are connected to transforming a company, like inflection points, scale changes, or critical transitions. The authors present practical business examples and an 8-step framework to implement their ideas in teams and on the individual level. This offers reflective practitioners a guideline for leveraging the enormous potential of weak signals for effective strategy development and operational execution in times of uncertainty – and gives them the competitive edge they need to succeed.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFührung. 4aKomplexität. 4aStrategische Früherkennung. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Leadership.2bisacsh  aLeadership in Complex Times.  aOrganizational Development.  aSmall Data versus Big Data.  aUniversal Power Laws.  aWeak Signals.1 aLambertz, Mark, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2023 Englishz978311131907008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2023z9783111318134oZDB-23-DBV0 cEPUBz97831107979230 cprintz978311079698840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311079788640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110797886423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110797886/original  a978-3-11-131907-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aE